      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i keep getting a MemoryError when i try to run this script that processes a huge csv file with pandas. i think it's because i'm loading the whole thing at once. what's the actual difference between using a list comprehension vs a generator function for handling these rows? i need to keep the memory usage low.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A **list comprehension** builds the entire collection in memory at once, like a big, overflowing pile of things. A **generator function**, on the other hand, is like a little pipe, only producing one item at a time when you ask for it. This is crucial when dealing with massive CSVs, because the generator doesn't need to store every single row in its memory, which keeps the memory usage low. If you use a generator, you'll be much happier than if you try to cram everything into a list.",
